    How customer reviews and ratings work

    Customer Reviews, including Product Star Ratings help customers to learn more about the product and decide whether it is the right product for them.

    To calculate the overall star rating and percentage breakdown by star, we don’t use a simple average. Instead, our system considers things like how recent a review is and if the reviewer bought the item on Amazon. It also analyzed reviews to verify trustworthiness.

    Amazon Customer
    5 out of 5 stars
    Worth it to me
    I've been in the market for a smartwatch for a while. I am very picky about the design and functionality. I love the look of the Samsung gear s3, just something about being able to spin the bezel reminds me about some of the watches I had when I was younger. So I was super stoked to find one one here on Amazon in the renewed section. Unfortunately this is an older model and was in acceptable condition but a steal at just 36.00. I noticed that the battery had a hard time keeping a charge and it would die within a few hours. Looking for accessories I found this replacement battery. It was pretty cheap and came with the tools to change it. It was not too difficult and took about 20 minutes start to finish to change. The hardest part for me was getting the back off without damaging the wires. Then putting it back together correctly. I would recommend taking some pictures before and during the process just to make it easier putting it back together. There is nothing solder it all just snapped back together easily. Put it on the charger and now it works better then ever and being 520ma the battery last almost twice as long. The only additional tools I use was a flat head screwdriver to gently pry the back off and a magnifying glass to be able to see the wire connections better. So now I'm into my watch for about 50bucks and absolutely love it. The only thing that I wish it would do is monitor my blood pressure but unfortunately living in the US the FDA regulates the ability and function of that here in the US, even on the newer versions of galaxy watches. Hope this helps if anyone is stuck on the fence of whether or not to buy an older smart watch.

    • Amazon Customer
      5.0 out of 5 stars I spent for the "like new" and couldn't tell it from new.
      Reviewed in the United States on March 13, 2023
      Verified Purchase
      I received a Fitbit in the first package, so was a little disappointed, but the seller responded immediately to phone/emails and sent the correct product out the same day.

      The watch was in generic packaging but there was not a single scratch or scuff on it, I couldn't tell it from new. The charger is aftermarket, I've never had a Samsung one to compare, but it charges the watch wirelessly in two hours from almost zero charge.

      Even being a new user and playing with it constantly, battery life is 20+hrs, I actually bought a second charger for work but haven't had to use it yet. I've used it as a phone a couple of times, it works well - I'm in IT so if I'm under a desk somewhere it's handy to have the call make/receive feature.

      I love getting my email and text on the watch, I'm able to respond by voice or quick reply without having to get my phone out, which is great. I really didn't think I'd be all that impressed as I usually wear a regular watch and bought it on a lark but I have grown to really like this watch.

      I didn't review the sleep tracking as I don't use the feature, but the other health features (heartbeat/steps/calories burned) seem spot on and have made me aware of my general health, the watch senses if you have been sitting for an hour plus and suggests you get up and move around or at least stretch at your desk.

      I even bought a metal band thinking I wouldn't be happy with the rubber band but have yet to fit it due to the comfort of the rubber band.

      After I downloaded two apps, the watch linked seamlessly with my Metro (T-Mobile) Motorola G Stylus that is itself a couple or three years old. The available apps and watch faces are all I need for now, overall a solid purchase.

      Overall, even though the watch is a few generations behind, I'm amazed at how happy I am with my purchase.
